This paper discusses the vulnerability of Deep Neural Networks in cyber security applications, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also focuses on crafting adversarial attacks, which involves optimization techniques and machine learning models, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
